  {
    "name": "glob",
    "description": "Enumerate workspace files matching a glob pattern.\n\nUse this when:\n- You need a list of files by name or extension (e.g. \"every Python file\n  in `pkg/`\").\n- You're narrowing scope before a more expensive operation (`grep`,\n  `read_file` per file).\n\nPrefer over:\n- `exec_command` with `find`/`ls` — `glob` returns structured output.\n\nDo NOT use for:\n- Searching file CONTENTS — use `grep`.\n- Recursive directory walks across hidden VCS data — `.git/`, `.svn/`,\n  etc. are excluded by design.\n- Following symlinks — symlinks are listed but not traversed.\n\nCapabilities and constraints:\n- Pattern is Python `fnmatch` style. `*` matches within a path segment;\n  `**` does NOT recurse — set `path=...` plus a `*.py`-style narrowing\n  instead.\n- Brace expansion (`{a,b}`) is NOT supported.\n- Leading-dot VCS directories are excluded.\n- Result set is capped at 100 paths. Narrow with `path=...` when\n  truncated.\n\nOutput shape:\n- `filenames`: workspace-relative matched paths.\n- `num_files`: count returned (post-cap).\n- `truncated`: True when the cap was hit.\n\nCommon pitfalls:\n- Expecting `**/*.py` to recurse — it does not. Use `path=\"src\"` and\n  `pattern=\"*.py\"`, or call `glob` from a deeper `path` to scope down.\n- Treating truncation as \"all results\" — check `truncated` before\n  assuming completeness.",
    "input_schema": {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
      "properties": {
        "path": {
          "default": null,
          "type": [
            "string",
            "null"
          ]
        },
        "pattern": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "pattern"
      ],
      "title": "GlobInput",
      "type": "object"
    },
    "output_schema": {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
      "properties": {
        "cwd": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "filenames": {
          "items": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "type": "array"
        },
        "num_files": {
          "format": "uint32",
          "minimum": 0.0,
          "type": "integer"
        },
        "pattern": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "truncated": {
          "type": "boolean"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "cwd",
        "filenames",
        "num_files",
        "pattern",
        "truncated"
      ],
      "title": "GlobOutput",
      "type": "object"
    }
  },
  {
    "name": "grep",
    "description": "Regex-scan workspace file contents.\n\nUse this when:\n- You need to find which files contain a pattern (`files_with_matches`\n  mode).\n- You need to count matches per file (`count` mode).\n- You need to extract matching lines for inspection (`content` mode).\n\nPrefer over:\n- `exec_command` with `grep`/`rg` — `grep` is cheaper, routed read-only, and\n  returns structured output.\n\nDo NOT use for:\n- Reading whole files — once you know the path, use `read_file`.\n- Enumerating files by name (no content match) — use `glob`.\n- Structural code search (AST-aware) — there is no `--type`-aware mode;\n  combine `glob` to narrow scope, then call `grep`.\n\nCapabilities and constraints:\n- Pattern is Python `re` regex (NOT PCRE2). Possessive quantifiers and\n  recursive groups are unsupported. Literal braces work without escaping.\n- VCS directories (`.git`/`.svn`/`.hg`/`.bzr`/`.jj`/`.sl`) are excluded.\n- Files larger than 10 MB and non-UTF-8 files are skipped silently.\n- Output is capped at 20 KB total content AND `head_limit` entries\n  (default 250; 0 = unlimited subject to the byte cap).\n- `multiline=True` enables `re.MULTILINE | re.DOTALL` — `.` matches\n  newlines, `^`/`$` match line boundaries.\n- `glob_filter` is fnmatch (e.g. `'*.py'`), not bash glob.\n\nOutput shape:\n- `mode`: \"files_with_matches\" | \"count\" | \"content\".\n- `filenames`: matched files in scan order.\n- `content`: rendered match content (`content` mode) or `path:count`\n  lines (`count` mode); empty in `files_with_matches` mode.\n- `num_files`, `num_lines`, `num_matches`: cardinalities.\n- `applied_limit`, `applied_offset`, `truncated`: paging signals.\n\nCommon pitfalls:\n- Forgetting `multiline=True` for cross-line patterns — the regex won't\n  match across newlines by default.\n- Over-broad scope: scanning the whole workspace for \"TODO\" returns\n  truncated output. Pass `path=...` or `glob_filter=...` to narrow first.\n- Confusing `head_limit=0` with \"no results\": 0 means \"unlimited\".\n\nExample:\n  # Find every place a symbol is defined\n  grep(pattern=r\"^class (Foo|Bar)\\b\", output_mode=\"content\",\n       line_numbers=True)",
    "input_schema": {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
      "definitions": {
        "GrepMode": {
          "description": "`output_mode` literal.",
          "enum": [
            "content",
            "files_with_matches",
            "count"
          ],
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      "properties": {
        "case_insensitive": {
          "default": false,
          "type": "boolean"
        },
        "glob_filter": {
          "default": null,
          "type": [
            "string",
            "null"
          ]
        },
        "head_limit": {
          "default": 250,
          "format": "uint32",
          "minimum": 0.0,
          "type": "integer"
        },
        "line_numbers": {
          "default": false,
          "type": "boolean"
        },
        "multiline": {
          "default": false,
          "type": "boolean"
        },
        "offset": {
          "default": 0,
          "format": "uint32",
          "minimum": 0.0,
          "type": "integer"
        },
        "output_mode": {
          "allOf": [
            {
              "$ref": "#/definitions/GrepMode"
            }
          ],
          "default": "files_with_matches"
        },
        "path": {
          "default": null,
          "type": [
            "string",
            "null"
          ]
        },
        "pattern": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "pattern"
      ],
      "title": "GrepInput",
      "type": "object"
    },
    "output_schema": {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
      "properties": {
        "applied_limit": {
          "format": "uint32",
          "minimum": 0.0,
          "type": [
            "integer",
            "null"
          ]
        },
        "applied_offset": {
          "format": "uint32",
          "minimum": 0.0,
          "type": "integer"
        },
        "content": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "cwd": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "filenames": {
          "items": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "type": "array"
        },
        "mode": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "num_files": {
          "format": "uint32",
          "minimum": 0.0,
          "type": "integer"
        },
        "num_lines": {
          "format": "uint32",
          "minimum": 0.0,
          "type": "integer"
        },
        "num_matches": {
          "format": "uint32",
          "minimum": 0.0,
          "type": "integer"
        },
        "pattern": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "truncated": {
          "type": "boolean"
        }
      },
      "required": [
        "applied_offset",
        "content",
        "cwd",
        "filenames",
        "mode",
        "num_files",
        "num_lines",
        "num_matches",
        "pattern",
        "truncated"
